messages.content: 112 is a whole number, an even number, and a composite number (meaning it has factors other than 1 and itself).  Its prime factorization is 2<sup>4</sup> x 7.  It's also divisible by 1, 2, 4, 7, 8, 14, 16, 28, 56, and 112.  In some contexts, it might represent a quantity, a measurement (e.g., 112 pounds), or a code (e.g., a phone number or an emergency number in some regions).
